# isync / mbsync — syncs Gmail IMAP <-> local Maildir at ~/.local/share/mail.
# Secrets are NEVER stored here: passwords come from `pass` at runtime.
#
# Per-machine one-time setup for each account (id == the email address):
#   pass insert email/<address>    # paste a Google App Password (not your login pw)
# Then:  mbsync -a                 # syncs every channel
#
# App Password: myaccount.google.com -> Security -> 2-Step Verification ->
# App passwords (requires 2FA). Some Workspace/edu orgs disable these; if so
# that account needs OAuth2 instead — ask and I'll convert it.

# ───────────────────────────── av@lab828.com ─────────────────────────────
IMAPAccount av@lab828.com
Host imap.gmail.com
Port 993
User av@lab828.com
PassCmd "pass show email/av@lab828.com"
TLSType IMAPS
AuthMechs LOGIN

IMAPStore av@lab828.com-remote
Account av@lab828.com

MaildirStore av@lab828.com-local
Subfolders Verbatim
Path ~/.local/share/mail/av@lab828.com/
Inbox ~/.local/share/mail/av@lab828.com/INBOX

Channel av@lab828.com
Far :av@lab828.com-remote:
Near :av@lab828.com-local:
Patterns "INBOX" "[Gmail]/Sent Mail" "[Gmail]/Drafts" "[Gmail]/Trash" "[Gmail]/All Mail"
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

